description.narrative: Authorities in selected subnational areas with high levels of neonatal mortality and chronic malnutrition utilize validated coordinating tools to guarantee access of children to integral and quality health and nutrition services, which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Nutrition â€“ General, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, children, particularly thosed aged 0-5, and prgnant women have increased access to quality health and nutrition services, healthy lifestyles and rearing practices that allow children to fully develop

description.narrative: UNICEF El Salvador has supported the national health system, including through its advocacy to promote awareness of children’s rights to receive quality maternal-health services, and has worked to encourage greater inter-and intra- multisectoral coordination of services that are scalable and sustainable. The design of cost-effective specialized tool kits to promote international and UNICEF endorsed quality care strategies have strengthened child, family-friendly, and adolescent care services, including those for the Child-friendly Hospital Initiative (IHAN) and Health Care Services Child and Mother-friendly (USANYM). | Status:Met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
